2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on the performance analysis of a cellular network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper studies the asymptotic properties of ASE, which can be seen as a system-level metric. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the ASE in the context of ultradense networks, which are expected to support high-bandwidth multimedia applications. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society): While the paper does not directly address social or ethical issues related to computing, it may have implications for the design and deployment of cellular networks, which can impact society.
